data.content:
Three things break in EF Core 10. Here's each issue and fix:

---

## 1. `ExecuteUpdateAsync` — expression tree no longer needed

The API now accepts a regular lambda (`Action`) instead of an `Expression<Func<...>>`. Your manual expression-tree construction won't compile. Replace with:

```csharp
await context.Blogs.ExecuteUpdateAsync(s =>
{
    s.SetProperty(b => b.Views, 8);
    if (nameChanged)
    {
        s.SetProperty(b => b.Name, "foo");
    }
});
```

---

## 2. Complex type column names are now uniquified

Two changes apply:
- **Duplicate property names** across complex types (e.g., `ShippingAddress.Street` and `BillingAddress.Street`) get a numeric suffix appended.
- **Nested complex types** use the full path: `Order.Payment.BillingAddress.City` → column `Payment_BillingAddress_City` (was `BillingAddress_City`).

Both generate rename migrations. To preserve existing column names, pin them explicitly:

```csharp
modelBuilder.Entity<Customer>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.ShippingAddress, sa =>
        sa.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("ShippingAddress_Street"));
    b.ComplexProperty(c => c.BillingAddress, ba =>
        ba.Property(a => a.Street).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_Street"));
});

// For nested:
modelBuilder.Entity<Order>(b => {
    b.ComplexProperty(o => o.Payment, p =>
        p.ComplexProperty(pay => pay.BillingAddress, ba =>
            ba.Property(a => a.City).HasColumnName("BillingAddress_City")));
});
```

---

## 3. `IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger` — new `logCommandText` parameter

All methods (e.g., `CommandReaderExecuting`) now require an additional `string logCommandText` parameter (redacted SQL for safe logging):

```csharp
public class MyLogger : IRelationalCommandDiagnosticsLogger
{
    public InterceptionResult<DbDataReader> CommandReaderExecuting(
        IRelationalConnection connection, DbCommand command,
        DbContext context, Guid commandId, Guid connectionId,
        DateTimeOffset startTime,
        string logCommandText)   // ← add this
    { /* logging — use logCommandText for safe output */ }
}
```

Update every method in the interface implementation to include the new parameter.
